{"id":1417,"date":"2020-06-30T06:14:47","date_gmt":"2020-06-30T06:14:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/?p=1417"},"modified":"2021-07-14T10:23:57","modified_gmt":"2021-07-14T10:23:57","slug":"elearning-web-app-development","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/elearning-web-app-development","title":{"rendered":"eLearning Web &#038; App Development Solutions: Essential Things You Need to Know?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today people search for everything online. If people have to find something, learn anything, or educate themselves they do it online. That&#8217;s why eLearning websites are needed. There are mainly three types of eLearning websites that are online learning platforms, eLearning marketplace, and learning web conferencing software.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Categorization of e-learning websites in Detail<\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Online Learning Platforms<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this type of website, users learn on their own. This platform provides content to users remotely and administrators track the progress of the user and after the course, completion provides the user with a certificate. Content can be delivered in the form of notes or in the form of videos where famous educators deliver the material in the form of episodes so that users can watch them and learn uniformly.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1974 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/2330461-1.jpg\" alt=\"E-Learning\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/2330461-1.jpg 750w, https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/2330461-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/06\/2330461-1-272x182.jpg 272w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eLearning Marketplace<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this platform, educators provide one-to-one classes to students. In this platform, students can choose their educators according to their course and subject. Students rely on the teachers to guide them throughout the course and that is supported by the interaction like quizzes, progress tracking options, and it also depends on the subject they operate in.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eLearning Web Conferencing Software\u00a0<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This platform is best for big masses for people who need to join other educators online to interact with one another. This is preferable among universities and educational establishments that want to connect large numbers of people into learning sessions.<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Importance of eLearning Marketplace<\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today the internet makes education available from anywhere and it even tempts modern students<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Various demographics and skills formed a new learning model<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Flexible and continuing education demand is growing<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The things you need to focus on when entering eLearning Marketplace<\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Deliver a united learning experience<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Connect with people and create an online learning community\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Try to student confidence in the field they want to specialize<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How to develop an eLearning Website or App<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Research about the target audience: Before <a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/custom-software-development\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">developing an eLearning website or app<\/a>, analyze your target audience. Answer a few questions like how you can improve the skills and knowledge of the user, which technology can help users to grow, what users are interested in learning, and what content should be used. This type of question helps you to keep the interest of your target audience in your mind.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Follow up your Competitors<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you know about your target audience, research which platforms have already targeted that audience and what features they are offering. By this, while developing your website or app you get an idea of which features and functionality should be added so you can stand out of the box from your competitors.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Quality Content<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Users should be able to find everything valuable. Your user should be engaged by your content. Your website should contain audio, video, infographics, text, and slides so users can perceive the information differently and acknowledge the variation your site provides. You can also include games to educate users in an entertaining way.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Communicate with Good Educators<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If content will be delivered by skilled educators that will create a brand image for your site. Only teachers who are passionate about their learning can inspire users for using your site. And skilled teachers can also be present as additional marketing tools.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Proper Assessment\u00a0<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your website should be providing regular assessments like regular tests and quizzes to help users track their development and achievements. Also, share the assessment and analytics of students&#8217; performance with educators. So they can adjust their content accordingly to the students.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">UX should be Excellent<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Make sure that the interface should be easy to access, have a simple layout, and all <a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/benefits-of-responsive-web-design\">website elements should be perfectly placed<\/a>. So that users can find everything easily and they should not be distracted by anything.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User Feedback<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your website should be giving students a chance to leave feedback about your websites, educators, and content used. This will give valuable insight into your site and help you to improve your learning space.<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Marketing your eLearning Site\u00a0<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You should know to market your eLearning application through different promotional strategies so that it can be known by the public. Marketing should include both online and offline methods.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">eLearning platforms are difficult and need a lot of attention. You should understand your target audience&#8217;s needs before presenting anything to them. Your website should be user-friendly as well as have relevant content, a reward system, a fun section, and a proper assessment.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/get-in-touch\" target=\"_blank\" rel